<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="62" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,601,152,178]" box="[151,601,152,178]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,601,152,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,601,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscorum">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,601,152,178]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Bombus muscorum</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,222,715]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
This bumblebee species has a Eurosiberian distribution. Due to a significant reduction of its distribution range, it is considered as Vulnerable in the 
<collectionCode box="[509,577,259,283]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">IUCN</collectionCode>
European Red List (Rasmont 
<emphasis box="[917,973,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,222,715]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
In the Iberian Peninsula it can be found in the northern half and at isolated areas in more southern points. Elevational distribution ranges between 410 and 
<quantity box="[698,783,331,355]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Castro" box="[798,939,331,355]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" refString="Castro, L. (1994) Sobre los Bombinae (Hymenoptera, Apidae) de la Sierra de Albarracin (II). Zapateri Revista aragonesa de entomologia, 4, 137 - 144." type="journal article" year="1994">Castro 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[950,1295,330,355]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" refString="Ornosa, C. &amp; Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. (2004) Hymenoptera: Apoidea I. In: Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Fol. 23. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 556." type="book chapter" year="2004">Ornosa &amp; Ortiz-Sánchez 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,222,715]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
At present it has been sampled in the Pyrenees foraging in forest pastures and open areas with scrub between 
<date box="[151,329,402,427]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" value="1280" valueMax="1660">
1280 and 
<quantity box="[273,329,402,427]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.66" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="1660.0">1660</quantity>
</date>
m (
<figureCitation box="[386,460,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), on 
<taxonomicName box="[528,757,402,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scabiosa">
<emphasis box="[528,757,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Centaurea scabiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[814,1028,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Digitalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis box="[814,1028,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Digitalis purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[1085,1307,402,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Echium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="21" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgare">
<emphasis box="[1085,1269,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Echium vulgare</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gouan" authorityName="Gouan" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Eryngium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bourgatii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Eryngium bourgatii</emphasis>
Gouan
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[352,563,438,463]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lotus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corniculatus">
<emphasis box="[352,563,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Lotus corniculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[611,809,438,463]" class="Aves" family="Prunellidae" genus="Prunella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[611,809,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Prunella vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1014,438,463]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acaulis">
<emphasis box="[856,1014,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Silene acaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Jacq. 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[1139,1382,438,463]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="21" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratense">
<emphasis box="[1139,1348,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Trifolium pratense</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[151,367,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis box="[151,336,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Trifolium repens</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,222,715]" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">
It is clearly a declining species in the Pyrenees (
<tableCitation box="[733,819,510,535]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1394,332,1883]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Bumblebee species and subspecies collected in the Pyrenees and IUCN category ranks (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC) of the extant bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees. The number of individuals sampled between 2006 and 2015 is indicated. In rare species and those with relevant records, the number of individuals known from historical literature or collections is included in brackets." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5" pageId="21" pageNumber="62" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF98FFBFFF3CFF45FADEFED5">Table 2</tableCitation>
), as well as the entire Iberian Peninsula, where it needs special attention and assessment and very likely, protection. According to the current data, this species exhibits greater orophilous tendency (
<figureCitation box="[479,547,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="62">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
